6:
I wonder if there was one back at 
home? I'd never heard of or seen 
anything like it though.
8:
Will I really be able to find my way 
back on this journey?
11:
I don't know... But I have to do 
something, right?
13:
Oh, I know! That Kaleidoscope place 
might have some answers.
15:
I still haven't seen much of what's 
there...
There may something there I haven't 
looked into yet!
19:
Maybe I should've told someone I was 
coming here.
No, Arisa... You can't keep relying on 
them for every little thing.
21:
Hopefully, I'll find some clues while I'm 
here.
24:
...I don't think you'll find anything of 
the sort, unfortunately.
31:
Nobody special... Just someone who 
wants to get even... with you.
34: With me? But I don't even know you.
37:
Don't you though? It was quite an 
endeavor, fixing up that hole you all 
tore.
39: I'm just here to get my dues.
44:
Look, I'm just trying to find my way 
back home, okay? So could you leave 
me alone?
48:
A way home, you say? There is 
nothing like that for you here—only 
a path... into the shadows.
52:
Unlikely as it may be... keep going, 
and you may very well just find the 
thing you're looking for. After all... 
you never know, right?
54:
I can't guarantee you'll come out the 
other side the same, however…
57:
I don't need your guarantees, weirdo. 
I'm just trying to find Losaria!
60:
Losaria? Now that's a pretty name... 
Is this truly the outcome you wish for?
67:
O darkness, slumbering in the void…
Reveal yourself to me—deepest of 
inner truths!
74:
After everything, you're still alive?
Or are you still waiting to be saved?
76: Isn't that what you've always wanted?
83:
You don't care about Losaria... 
This is just about yourself. It always 
has been.
91:
I... I have to save Losaria! She's 
waiting for me, I'm sure of it!
94:
Why? Did it vex you so that she's the 
one that had to save YOU all the time?
98:
It must have indeed. Oh, how pitiful... 
Are you trying to prove yourself to 
her?
100:
A shame, though, isn't it? There's no 
Losaria here for you to prove your 
worth to.
109:
You would do well to forget those you 
left behind.
111:
Singularity. You've disrupted this 
world with your presence, yet you can 
still prove your worth... to me.
117:
Losaria doesn't need someone like 
you. Why would she? You know good 
and well she's more than capable of 
handling herself.
119:
Yes, indeed... Forget about her. In THIS 
world, you need serve only me!
130:
Even... even if that were true! I'm still 
going to keep getting stronger for her!
133:
...And one day, I'll be just as strong as 
she was!
149:
Damn busybodies...
So... I see you've made your choice, 
elf.
152:
...That's right.
I don't care what you say about me—
I know that I'll be able to stand proudly
next to Losaria someday!
153:
And I won't have any more of what 
you have to say!
Elvish Bow!
170:
Why'd you come to a place like this 
on your own? Do you have any idea 
how worried we were?!
183:
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to make you 
worry.
191:
I don't know. He just came out of 
nowhere, calling me a singularity or 
whatever.
194:
...But he also knew of Losaria 
somehow.
199:
I don't know what he told you, but 
I can tell you one thing.
201:
You will see Losaria again one day. I'm 
sure she's waiting for you somewhere.
208:
I'm here for you, Arisa. So please don't 
go off on your own.
213:
And you're right... I promised that I'd 
introduce you all to her, didn't I?
217:
As long as I have my friends here, 
I know things will turn out okay. Just 
wait a little longer, Losaria!
